# ============================================================================
# Rule 14 - Plugin Architecture Standards
# ============================================================================

## Purpose

The AI Sales Employee Platform is a plugin-based SaaS platform.

Platform Core

↓

Industry Plugin

↓

Tenant Configuration

↓

Business Customization

Platform Core must never depend on a specific industry.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Platform Philosophy

Platform provides

Authentication

Authorization

Workflow

AI

Notifications

Media

Billing

Conversation

Customer

Lead

Reporting

Plugin provides

Business Rules

Catalog

Fields

Validation

AI Prompts

Workflow Extensions

Industry Integrations

Never mix these responsibilities.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Core Principle

Platform

Must know

Nothing

About

Real Estate

Education

Healthcare

Insurance

Automobile

Banking

All industry knowledge belongs inside plugins.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin Examples

Supported

Real Estate Plugin

Automobile Plugin

Education Plugin

Healthcare Plugin

Insurance Plugin

Recruitment Plugin

Travel Plugin

Future industries

Must require

No Platform Core modification.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Platform Core Responsibilities

Core owns

Authentication

Authorization

Users

Tenants

Organizations

Workflow Engine

AI Engine

Notification Engine

Conversation Engine

Media Engine

Billing

Audit

Observability

Plugin Registry

Configuration

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin Responsibilities

Plugin owns

Business Catalog

Business Rules

Custom Entities

Validation

Prompt Templates

Workflow Extensions

Industry Integrations

Reports

Dashboards

Search Filters

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin Isolation

Plugins

Must not

Access another plugin's database

Modify another plugin

Depend on another plugin implementation

Communicate only through

Contracts

Events

Extension Points

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Extension Points

Platform exposes

REST Contracts

Events

Plugin SDK

Workflow Hooks

AI Hooks

Notification Hooks

Validation Hooks

Search Hooks

Never modify Platform Core for a new plugin.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin SDK

Plugins interact with Platform only through SDKs.

Examples

plugin-sdk

workflow-sdk

notification-sdk

event-sdk

ai-sdk

media-sdk

Never access internal platform classes directly.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Database Ownership

Each plugin owns

Its own schema

or

Its own database

Never

Share plugin tables

Share plugin repositories

Cross-plugin joins

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# AI Extensions

Plugins may contribute

Prompt Templates

Knowledge Bases

Embedding Sources

AI Tools

Recommendation Rules

Prompt Versions

Platform AI executes them.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Workflow Extensions

Plugins may register

Workflow Steps

Business Rules

Human Tasks

Timers

Compensation Logic

Platform Workflow Engine coordinates execution.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Event Extensions

Plugins may publish

Industry Events

Example

PropertyListed

VehicleSold

StudentEnrolled

PolicyIssued

PatientRegistered

Platform events remain generic.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# UI Extensions

Plugins may contribute

Menus

Pages

Forms

Dashboards

Widgets

Reports

Platform UI loads dynamically.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Configuration

Every plugin

Supports

Enable

Disable

Tenant Scope

Version

Configuration

Feature Flags

Never require redeployment to enable a plugin.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Tenant Plugin Assignment

Each tenant

May enable

One

or

Many

Plugins

Example

Tenant A

Real Estate

Tenant B

Education

Tenant C

Insurance

Tenant D

Real Estate

+

Insurance

Platform supports multiple plugin combinations.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin Versioning

Every plugin

Has

pluginId

version

minimumPlatformVersion

supportedPlatformVersion

migrationVersion

Never overwrite plugin versions.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin Lifecycle

States

INSTALLED

REGISTERED

ENABLED

DISABLED

UPGRADING

FAILED

UNINSTALLED

Never invent additional lifecycle states without approval.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Security

Plugins

Must inherit

Authentication

Authorization

RBAC

Tenant Isolation

Audit

Plugins cannot weaken platform security.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Observability

Every plugin

Exports

Metrics

Logs

Tracing

Health

Business Metrics

Platform dashboards include plugin metrics.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Performance

Plugins

Must be

Lazy Loaded

Stateless

Horizontally Scalable

Cache Aware

Never reduce platform startup performance significantly.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Testing

Every plugin

Requires

Unit Tests

Integration Tests

Contract Tests

Compatibility Tests

Upgrade Tests

Tenant Isolation Tests

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Backward Compatibility

Plugins

Must support

Rolling Upgrades

Backward Compatible APIs

Event Versioning

Migration Scripts

Avoid breaking existing tenants.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Plugin Packaging

Recommended structure

plugins/

  real-estate-plugin/

  automobile-plugin/

  education-plugin/

  healthcare-plugin/

  insurance-plugin/

Each plugin contains

domain

application

api

events

workflow

ai

config

resources

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Review Checklist

Before approving verify

✓ No Core Modification

✓ Correct SDK Usage

✓ Database Isolation

✓ Tenant Isolation

✓ Event Compatibility

✓ Workflow Extension

✓ AI Extension

✓ Versioning

✓ Security

✓ Observability

✓ Performance

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Agent Decision Tree

Before generating a feature ask

1. Is this platform functionality?
2. Is this industry functionality?
3. Can this become a plugin?
4. Does Platform Core need modification?
5. Is an extension point sufficient?
6. Is an SDK available?
7. Does the plugin own its data?
8. Is tenant isolation preserved?
9. Is the plugin independently deployable?
10. Is backward compatibility maintained?

If Platform Core must change for an industry-specific feature

STOP

Redesign using a plugin extension.

Never couple Platform Core to a business domain.